io.spine.protobuf

Class AnyPacker

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.spine.protobuf.AnyPacker

  • public final class AnyPacker
extends java.lang.Object
    Utilities for packing messages into Any and unpacking them.

    When packing, the AnyPacker takes care of obtaining correct type URL prefix for the passed messages.

    When unpacking, the AnyPacker obtains Java class matching the type URL from the passed Any.

    See Also:
    Any.pack(Message, String), Any.unpack(Class)

      • unpack

        public static <T extends com.google.protobuf.Message> T unpack(com.google.protobuf.Any any,
                                                               java.lang.Class<T> cls)
        Unwraps Any value into an instance of the passed class.

        If there is no Java class for the type, UnexpectedTypeException is thrown.

        Type Parameters:
        T - the type enclosed into Any
        Parameters:
        any - instance of Any that should be unwrapped
        cls - the class implementing the type of the enclosed object
        Returns:
        unwrapped message instance
        Implementation Note:
        Protobuf Any.unpack(Class) isn't used by this implementation, since it creates a redundant default Message instance in its internal is(Class) sub-call. We are aiming for better performance and lower memory footprint. Therefore, we use the same default instance of the target Message to both verify the type name (complying is(Class) sub-call) and parse its contents.

      • unpackFunc

        public static <T extends com.google.protobuf.Message> java.util.function.Function<com.google.protobuf.Any,T> unpackFunc(java.lang.Class<T> type)
        Provides the function for unpacking messages of a given type from Any.

        The function returns null for null input.

        The function throws a UnexpectedTypeException if the actual type of the message does not match the given class.

        Parameters:
        type - expected class of the messages
